This paper deals with the problem of distinguishing credible from fake news, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it collects and releases datasets for research purposes. Additionally, the use of embeddings and DBPedia data suggests a focus on semantic analysis, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of machine learning models and feature engineering suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
